"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838577","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-20","<p>Public Health England supports local areas in responding to the threat from fentanyl, and other drugs. This includes ensuring wider availability of the opioid-overdose antidote naloxone, providing messages to use with people at risk, and issuing public health alerts when there is sufficient evidence of harm from particular drugs like fentanyl.</p><p>Local authorities are responsible for commissioning drug treatment services and interventions to reduce drug-related harm, based on local need.</p><p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Home Secretary has also asked the Advisory Council on the Misuse of Drugs to investigate the risks around fentanyl analogues, so we can maximise the effectiveness of our response.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-02-20T17:15:49.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838577/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838577/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-07","Fentanyl","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what strategy the Government has put in place to (a) support people affected by Fentanyl and (b) reduce the harm associated with that drug.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","127397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838578","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-20","<p>This information is not available centrally, and could be researched only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC has published guidance to help and support employers with the hash validation process. HMRC continue to work with customers to help and support employer education to improve the accuracy and timeliness of RTI data.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","127399","2018-02-20T15:52:18.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838578/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838578/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838578/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-07","PAYE","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many Real Time Information hashes have been sent by the BACS payment scheme to HMRC in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","127398"
