"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838643","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-26","<p>As set out in paragraph 4.7 of the Government Response to the Naylor Review, NHS Improvement will provide specialist support and guidance on areas such as contract management, as part of their National Health Service estates policy and technical guidance programme.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-02-26T14:45:22.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838643/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/838643/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-07","NHS Property and Estates Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to paragraph 4.7 of the Government Response to the Naylor Review, published on 30 January 2018, whether specialist support and guidance to the NHS for areas such as contract management will be provided by NHS staff and not by external management consultancies.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","127463"
